				\begin{document}$${\text{Suitability}} = 0.70 \cdot {\text{land use}} + 0.20 \cdot {\text{aspect}} + 0.10 \cdot {\text{slope}}$$\end{document}

Using GHI data provided by NREL (2012a, b), the annual terawatt hours (TWh/year) of solar energy available for utility-scale solar PV development on suitable lands was calculated. This was accomplished by multiplying the solar resource layer by a binary suitable land layer (with values of 1 where suitability values are above the selected minimum and 0 elsewhere), as shown in Eq. (2). The geographical potential was calculated at three minimum suitability rankings: 50, 70, and 90.2Total annual energyTWhyear=State∑B·GHIkWhm2·day·365daysyear·cell area900m2·conversion factor10-9TWhkWh\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
